  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The graph of a system of equations consists of the lines obtained by graphing each equation. Rewriting x + 2y = 8 in slope-intercept form gives y = &minus;(1/2)x + 4, a line with slope &minus;1/2 and y-intercept 4. Rewriting 2x &minus; y = 1 gives y = 2x &minus; 1, a line with slope 2 and y-intercept &minus;1. The graph in choice C shows exactly these two lines, which intersect at (2, 3) — the solution of the system.</p><p>Choices A, B, and D each contain at least one line with the wrong slope or wrong y-intercept and therefore do not represent this system.</p>",
